					<a href="//dealbook.nytimes.com/2013/07/31/an-analysis-finds-a-bias-for-banks-in-s-p-ratings/?ref=dealbook"><img src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2013/07/30/business/dbpix-ratings/dbpix-ratings-thumbWide.jpg" width="190" height="126" alt="Banks Find S.&amp;P. More Favorable in Bond Ratings" /></a>
				</div>
                				<h4><a href="//dealbook.nytimes.com/2013/07/31/an-analysis-finds-a-bias-for-banks-in-s-p-ratings/?ref=dealbook">Banks Find S.&P. More Favorable in Bond Ratings</a></h4>
				<p class="nyt-article-byline">By NATHANIEL POPPER</p>
				<p class="nyt-article-summary">Standard and Poorâs has been giving higher ratings than its big rivals to certain mortgage-backed securities, and its market share has tripled in the first half of 2013, an analysis shows.</p>
			</div>
			
